      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i think i might be able to check it myself if i'm careful. you mentioned a capacitor... how would i tell if that's actually the part that's broken? like is there a specific sign or something i should look for when i open the panel?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A capacitor, when it's failing, often shows signs of bulging, leaking fluid, or having visible scorch marks on its casing. If you can safely access it, you might notice it looks swollen or has a brownish, oily residue around the edges. Sometimes, a simple multimeter test can confirm its capacitance value, but if you're unsure about using the meter, just visually inspecting for damage is a good starting point. Remember, even if you're just looking, treat it like a high-voltage area!",
